Silver birch; The understorey vegetation in the Scots pine and silver birch plots consisted of suppressed trees (e.g. P. abies, Fagus sylvatica, Quercus robur, Sorbus aucuparia, B. pendula), bushes (e.g. Frangula alnus) and well-developed field layers of e.g. Vaccinium myrtillus, Vaccinium vitis-idaea, Deschampsia flexuosa, Calluna vulgaris and Agrostis capillaris.
